{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775830727984,"sessionID":"ses_2884073faffeGkgZBLhfZx1tsf","part":{"id":"prt_d77bfab19001lc4gRkC1uMV2m8","messageID":"msg_d77bf9ec7001qlkRYtmYPEosCn","sessionID":"ses_2884073faffeGkgZBLhfZx1tsf","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_ca4e59655eb844bbb6a9ca3b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube router code","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark to understand the router module and JWT-related code. I need to find:\n\n1. All files under pkg/router/ - read their contents\n2. Any existing JWT, auth, token, middleware related code in the project\n3. The project's existing middleware patterns\n4. Any existing auth configuration or JWT settings\n5. The main entry point and how the router is set up\n6. Any existing OpenSpec or spec files to understand the format used\n\nSearch broadly for: jwt, token, auth, middleware, router, gin, echo, http handler patterns.\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The router module structure and current implementation\n- Any existing auth/JWT code\n- How routes are registered\n- The web framework used (gin, echo, standard lib, etc.)\n- Existing middleware patterns\n- Configuration patterns used in the project\n- Any existing spec files and their format","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288403cc8ffegXZW3OxxUTpAhi (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive summary of the AgentCube project, focusing on the router module, JWT/auth code, middleware patterns, and spec formats.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Analysis: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**AgentCube** (`github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`) is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle.\n\n**Go version:** 1.25.0\n**Module path:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Router Module Structure (`pkg/router/`)\n\nThe router module consists of **12 Go source files** (no test files exist yet):\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/config.go` | 32 | `Config` struct with defaults (Port, Debug, TLS, MaxConcurrentRequests, session timeouts, StoreType) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/server.go` | 139 | `Server` struct, `NewServer()`, `registerRoutes()`, `Start()`, `Run()`, `Shutdown()` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/router.go` | 79 | `Router` interface (`AddRoute`, `RemoveRoute`, `ServeHTTP`) + `routerImpl` with mutex-protected route map |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/session_manager.go` | 176 | `SessionManager` interface + `manager` impl (session CRUD, sandbox creation via WorkloadManager HTTP calls) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go` | 129 | `JWTManager` -- RS256 token generation, RSA-2048 key bootstrap, K8s Secret persistence |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/proxy.go` | 192 | Reverse proxy logic, `handleInvoke`, `handleAgentInvoke`, `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke`, `forwardToSandbox` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go` | 55 | `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `RequestLoggerMiddleware`, `TraceIDMiddleware` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/health.go` | 18 | `GET /health/live` and `GET /health/ready` handlers |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/informer.go` | 84 | `InformerManager` -- SharedInformerFactory for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter CRDs (event handlers are stubs -- only log) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/backend.go` | 92 | `Backend` struct, `BackendHealthChecker` with consecutive fail/success thresholds |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/loadbalancer.go` | 100 | `LoadBalancer` interface, `RoundRobinBalancer`, `LeastConnectionsBalancer` |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/errors.go` | 45 | `SessionNotFoundError`, `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError`, `SessionTerminatedError` |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Web Framework: **Gin**\n\nThe project uses **`github.com/gin-gonic/gin` v1.10.0** as its HTTP framework throughout both the Router and WorkloadManager modules.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Route Registration (How Routes Are Set Up)\n\nRoutes are registered in `server.go` via `registerRoutes()`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) registerRoutes() {\n    // Health endpoints -- NO middleware, publicly accessible\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health/live\", handleHealthLive)\n    s.engine.GET(\"/health/ready\", s.handleHealthReady)\n\n    // /v1 group -- with middleware stack\n    v1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1\")\n    v1.Use(gin.Logger())\n    v1.Use(gin.Recovery())\n    v1.Use(ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests))\n\n    // Invocation routes\n    v1.GET(\"/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n    v1.POST(\"/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleAgentInvoke)\n    v1.GET(\"/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n    v1.POST(\"/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path\", s.handleCodeInterpreterInvoke)\n}\n```\n\n**Key observation:** There is currently **NO AuthMiddleware** on the `/v1` routes. All invocation endpoints are unprotected.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Existing JWT/Auth Code\n\n#### 5a. JWTManager (jwt.go) -- Outbound Signing ONLY\n\nThe existing `JWTManager` handles **outbound token signing** (Router --> Sandbox/PicoD), but has **NO inbound token validation**:\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**Key capabilities:**\n- `NewJWTManager()` -- generates RSA-2048 key pair\n- `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)` -- creates RS256 JWT with `exp`, `iat`, `iss: \"agentcube-router\"` plus custom claims\n- `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` -- persists/loads keys from K8s Secret `picod-router-identity` in namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env var (or `default`)\n\n**Constants:**\n- `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n- `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n- `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n- `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n- `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n\n**What is MISSING:**\n- No `PublicKey()` getter method (needed for inbound validation)\n- No `ParseAndValidateToken()` method\n- No `AuthMiddleware` gin handler\n\n#### 5b. JWT Injection in Proxy (proxy.go)\n\nJWT tokens are injected into outbound requests to sandboxes in the `forwardToSandbox` Director:\n\n```go\nif kind == types.SandboxKind || kind == types.SandboxClaimKind {\n    if s.jwtManager != nil {\n        token, err := s.jwtManager.GenerateToken(map[string]interface{}{\n            \"session_id\": sessionID,\n        })\n        req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Existing Middleware Patterns\n\nAll middleware follows the `gin.HandlerFunc` pattern in `middleware.go`:\n\n**ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware** (semaphore-based rate limiting):\n```go\nfunc ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    sem := make(chan struct{}, maxConcurrent)\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        select {\n        case sem <- struct{}{}:\n            defer func() { <-sem }()\n            c.Next()\n        default:\n            c.JSON(429, gin.H{\"error\": \"server overloaded...\", \"code\": \"SERVER_OVERLOADED\"})\n            c.Abort()\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**RequestLoggerMiddleware** (structured logging with slog):\n```go\nfunc RequestLoggerMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        start := time.Now()\n        c.Next()\n        slog.Info(\"request\", \"method\", ..., \"status\", ..., \"duration_ms\", ..., \"trace_id\", ...)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**TraceIDMiddleware** (UUID injection):\n```go\nfunc TraceIDMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        traceID := uuid.New().String()\n        c.Request.Header.Set(\"X-Trace-Id\", traceID)\n        c.Writer.Header().Set(\"X-Trace-Id\", traceID)\n        c.Next()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Middleware application pattern:** Applied at the group level via `v1.Use(...)`.\n\n**WorkloadManager middleware** (in `pkg/workloadmanager/`): The `middleware/` directory exists but is empty. The `response/` package provides unified response helpers (`JSON`, `Created`, `Error`, `ErrorWithID`).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Configuration Patterns\n\n**Config struct** (`config.go`):\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string\n    Debug                 bool\n    EnableTLS             bool\n    TLSCert               string\n    TLSKey                string\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int\n    SessionCheckInterval  time.Duration\n    SessionIdleTimeout    time.Duration\n    SessionMaxDuration    time.Duration\n    StoreType             string\n}\n```\n\n**Defaults** via `NewDefaultConfig()`:\n- Port: `\"8080\"`\n- Debug: `false`\n- EnableTLS: `false`\n- MaxConcurrentRequests: `1000`\n- SessionCheckInterval: `5 * time.Minute`\n- SessionIdleTimeout: `30 * time.Minute`\n- SessionMaxDuration: `24 * time.Hour`\n- StoreType: `\"\"`\n\n**Environment variables used:**\n- `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` -- required by SessionManager\n- `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` -- JWT secret namespace (default: `\"default\"`)\n- `STORE_TYPE` -- store backend selection (redis/valkey)\n\n**CLI flags** (planned but not implemented -- no `cmd/` directory exists):\n- `-port`, `-debug`, `-enable-tls`, `-tls-cert`, `-tls-key`, `-max-concurrent-requests`\n\n---\n\n### 8. TDD Test Requirements for Auth (from testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md)\n\nThe manifest defines these Router auth tests that must pass:\n\n```\n## 2. Router (Go) - High Concurrency & Security Tests\n- Middleware: AuthMiddleware\n    - Test-RT-1: Construct invalid JWT, verify 401 Unauthorized\n    - Test-RT-2: Construct expired JWT, verify \"Token Expired\" response\n- Proxy Logic: HandleProxy\n    - Test-RT-3: Simulate backend timeout, verify Gateway Timeout handling\n    - Test-RT-4: Verify header passthrough (Host, X-Forwarded-For, etc.)\n```\n\nPhysical requirements:\n- T/C Ratio must be > 0.4\n- Every `*.go` file must have a corresponding `*_test.go` file\n\n---\n\n### 9. Spec File Format (OpenSpec Pattern)\n\nSpec files follow a **Gherkin-style** format with `Requirement` and `Scenario` blocks:\n\n**Location:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/` and `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/<module>/`\n\n**Available spec files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/spec.md` -- Session routing requirements\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-routing/design.md` -- Session routing design\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` -- Sandbox orchestration\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/sandbox-orchestration/design.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/code-execution/spec.md` -- PicoD code execution\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/session-store/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/deployment/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/ci-cd/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/python-sdk/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/idle-cleanup/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/integrations/spec.md`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/specs/test_spec.md`\n\n**Spec format pattern:**\n```markdown\n# <Module> Specification\n\n## Purpose\n<One-paragraph description>\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: <Requirement name>\nThe system SHALL <behavior description>.\n\n#### Scenario: <Scenario name>\n- **GIVEN** <precondition>\n- **WHEN** <action>\n- **THEN** <expected outcome>\n```\n\n**Design doc format** (`design.md`):\n- Module header with go.mod info\n- Go code snippets for structs, interfaces, constants\n- Route tables (Method | Path | Middleware | Handler)\n- Dependency lists\n- Environment variable tables\n\n**Change request format** (`changes/AR-XXX/`):\nEach AR directory contains: `proposal.md`, `delta-spec.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md`\n\n---\n\n### 10. Summary of Key Findings for JWT Auth Implementation\n\n1. **No inbound auth exists** -- All `/v1` routes are completely unprotected\n2. **JWTManager already exists** with RS256 signing capability and K8s Secret key persistence\n3. **JWTManager lacks validation methods** -- needs `PublicKey()` and `ParseAndValidateToken()` additions\n4. **Middleware pattern is established** -- `gin.HandlerFunc` returning closures, applied via `group.Use()`\n5. **Error response format** uses `gin.H{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": \"...\"}` pattern\n6. **TDD manifest requires** `Test-RT-1` (invalid JWT -> 401) and `Test-RT-2` (expired JWT -> \"Token Expired\")\n7. **PicoD already has AuthMiddleware** (per code-execution spec) that can serve as a reference pattern -- it validates Bearer tokens with RSA public key, rejects non-RSA methods, uses `WithExpirationRequired`, `WithIssuedAt`, and `WithLeeway(1 minute)`\n8. **Health endpoints must remain public** -- `/health/live` and `/health/ready` should NOT require auth\n9. **No `cmd/router/main.go` exists** -- no CLI entry point yet\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288403cc8ffegXZW3OxxUTpAhi","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube router code","time":{"start":1775830549300,"end":1775830727981}}}}
